title: Tel-Aviv Cafe
typeOfFood: Vegan, Mediterranean, Take-out, Middle Eastern, Kosher, Israeli
description: Est. 2010 as vegetarian then turned all-vegan in 2016. Bistro offering Mediterranean and Israeli cuisines. Bright interior with modern decor. Food is sugar-free with gluten-free options. Sample items might be breakfast sets with apricot butter, ras el hanout chutney, tempeh camembert, soy shwarma, tofu kofta kebab, and hummus.
